definition.value: A mannotriose consisting of two beta-D-mannopyranose residues and a D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by (1->4) and (1->3) glycosidic bonds.
A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of two alpha-D-mannopyranose residues and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucitol joined in sequence by (1->2) and (1->3) glycosidic bonds.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose, alpha-D-glucopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->6) and (1->2) glycosidic bonds.
A glucotriose consisting of three beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->3) and (1->6) glycosidic bonds.

An amino trisaccharide that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 6 have been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl and alpha-L-fucopyranosyl derivatives, respectively.
A disaccharide that is D-mannitol in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into its alpha-D-galactopyranoside
